column9:
Consider extracting the complex filter condition into a separate function for better readability and maintainability. For example:
```typescript
function isTopLevelCommentInHunk(comment: ReviewComment, file: File, hunk: Hunk): boolean {
  const isInHunkRange = (line: number) => line <= hunk.endLine && line >= hunk.startLine;
  return !comment.in_reply_to_id && 
         comment.path === file.filename && 
         comment.body.length && 
         comment.line && 
         isInHunkRange(comment.line) &&
         (!comment.start_line || isInHunkRange(comment.start_line));
}
```

