The current implementation might throw errors if `PAYLOAD_TAG_OPEN` or `PAYLOAD_TAG_CLOSE` are not found in the comment body, as `split()[1]` would return undefined. Consider adding more robust error handling:
```typescript
const parts = overviewComment.body?.split(PAYLOAD_TAG_OPEN) || [];
if (parts.length < 2) {
  warning('Missing payload open tag');
  return { commits: [] };
}
const payloadParts = parts[1].split(PAYLOAD_TAG_CLOSE);
if (payloadParts.length < 1) {
  warning('Missing payload close tag');
  return { commits: [] };
}
const payload = JSON.parse(payloadParts[0] || '{}');
```

